{"title":"Imbalanced Data Project Tutorial","html":"<h1 id=\"imbalanced-data-project-tutorial\">Imbalanced Data Project Tutorial</h1>\n<p>Step-by-step tutorial for handling imbalanced data.</p>\n<h2 id=\"project-fraud-detection\">Project: Fraud Detection</h2>\n<h3 id=\"step-1-analyze-imbalance\">Step 1: Analyze Imbalance</h3>\n<pre class=\"shiki dark-plus\" style=\"background-color:#1E1E1E;color:#D4D4D4\" tabindex=\"0\"><code><span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#C586C0\">from</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\"> collections </span><span style=\"color:#C586C0\">import</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\"> Counter</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">counter = Counter(y)</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#DCDCAA\">print</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">(counter)</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"></span></code></pre>\n<h3 id=\"step-2-apply-smote\">Step 2: Apply SMOTE</h3>\n<pre class=\"shiki dark-plus\" style=\"background-color:#1E1E1E;color:#D4D4D4\" tabindex=\"0\"><code><span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#C586C0\">from</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\"> imblearn.over_sampling </span><span style=\"color:#C586C0\">import</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\"> SMOTE</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">smote = SMOTE(</span><span style=\"color:#9CDCFE\">random_state</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">=</span><span style=\"color:#B5CEA8\">42</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">)</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">X_resampled, y_resampled = smote.fit_resample(X_train, y_train)</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"></span></code></pre>\n<h3 id=\"step-3-train-and-evaluate\">Step 3: Train and Evaluate</h3>\n<pre class=\"shiki dark-plus\" style=\"background-color:#1E1E1E;color:#D4D4D4\" tabindex=\"0\"><code><span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">model = RandomForestClassifier(</span><span style=\"color:#9CDCFE\">class_weight</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">=</span><span style=\"color:#CE9178\">'balanced'</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">)</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">model.fit(X_resampled, y_resampled)</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"></span></code></pre>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Congratulations!</strong> You've handled imbalanced data!</p>\n","source":"20-handling-imbalanced-data/imbalanced-data-project-tutorial.md","githubUrl":"https://github.com/NabidAlam/road-to-machine-learning/blob/main/20-handling-imbalanced-data/imbalanced-data-project-tutorial.md","module":"20-handling-imbalanced-data","lessonId":"imbalanced-data-project-tutorial","guideId":null,"type":"module"}